WEBVTT

00:00.515 --> 00:02.049
<i>Previously on:</i>

00:02.153 --> 00:05.070
I am determined to find someone
who wants to be with me

00:05.072 --> 00:06.989
for who I am,
not what I have.

00:06.991 --> 00:08.607
I need to buy a little
bit of everything.

00:08.609 --> 00:09.908
I can help you out with that.

00:09.910 --> 00:12.194
I appreciate it... Kate.

00:12.196 --> 00:15.748
Not a problem...
Sam Wilson.

00:15.750 --> 00:16.915
It's refreshing,

00:16.917 --> 00:19.501
talking to someone like you
for a change.

00:19.503 --> 00:20.586
Someone like me?

00:20.588 --> 00:22.571
Yeah, someone who's not
constantly trying

00:22.573 --> 00:24.456
to impress me
with how much stuff he's got.

00:24.458 --> 00:26.458
Kate, this is
my friend Alan.

00:26.460 --> 00:28.410
Thanks so much
for picking us up.

00:28.412 --> 00:29.962
Yeah, this clown
rents a room from me,

00:29.964 --> 00:31.630
suddenly I'm running
a taxi service.

00:31.632 --> 00:32.765
You should move out.

00:32.767 --> 00:33.966
Can't afford to.

00:33.968 --> 00:35.917
Maybe you could crash here.

00:35.919 --> 00:37.085
Have you really
thought this through?

00:37.087 --> 00:38.804
I've got to see where
this goes with Kate.

00:38.806 --> 00:40.939
Promise me one thing.
What's that?

00:40.941 --> 00:42.975
That we're always honest
with each other.

00:42.977 --> 00:44.777
You got it.

00:47.096 --> 00:48.280
Anyways, I hope that it's okay

00:48.282 --> 00:49.782
that I have people over
on Christmas.

00:49.784 --> 00:51.617
It's just Jake
and Lyndsey and my mom.

00:51.619 --> 00:52.868
Of course.
It's the holidays.

00:52.870 --> 00:54.419
It's the time to be
with the ones you love.

00:54.421 --> 00:56.405
Right. Uh, and my mom.

00:56.407 --> 01:01.109
So, uh, so listen, Sam Wilson,
how are things in Poorville?

01:01.111 --> 01:02.878
Are you <i>Les Misérables?</i>

01:02.880 --> 01:04.530
Actually, it's a hoot.

01:06.283 --> 01:08.250
You know,
last night

01:08.252 --> 01:10.385
Kate and I went shopping
at the 99 Cent Store.

01:10.387 --> 01:12.054
That place is amazing.

01:12.056 --> 01:14.923
Did you know that everything
there is 99 cents?

01:14.925 --> 01:18.343
Know it? I registered there
for my wedding.

01:18.345 --> 01:20.395
Two cans of peaches: 99 cents.

01:20.397 --> 01:22.631
Four-pack of yogurt: 99 cents.

01:22.633 --> 01:24.600
This owl-shaped mug?

01:24.602 --> 01:26.652
99 cents.

01:26.654 --> 01:28.604
Guess how much
the wine inside was?

01:28.606 --> 01:31.240
Uh, I'm going to go out
on a limb and say 99 cents?

01:31.242 --> 01:33.242
79 cents.

01:34.244 --> 01:35.861
Dented box.

01:35.863 --> 01:38.030
From now on, I'm buying
everything from that place.

01:38.032 --> 01:39.164
Uh, not condoms.

01:39.166 --> 01:41.250
I think that's how
I ended up with Jake.

01:41.252 --> 01:42.534
Hey.

01:42.536 --> 01:44.169
Hey, baby.

01:44.171 --> 01:45.337
Uh, I gotta go.

01:45.339 --> 01:46.672
Oh, hey, Katie.

01:46.674 --> 01:47.956
Alan.

01:47.958 --> 01:49.091
How are you?

01:49.093 --> 01:50.325
I'm fine-- just, uh...

01:50.327 --> 01:53.262
sipping some wine I got
at the 999 Dollar Store.

01:54.547 --> 01:56.831
Bye, Alan.

01:56.833 --> 01:58.550
Douche.

01:58.552 --> 01:59.935
Don't worry about him.

01:59.937 --> 02:01.186
How was your day?

02:01.188 --> 02:02.671
It's Christmas, Sam.

02:02.673 --> 02:05.524
Happy people wishing you
"Peace on Earth."

02:05.526 --> 02:07.476
It was horrible.

02:07.478 --> 02:09.561
Okay, somebody's got
a case of the Grinches.

02:09.562 --> 02:11.597
No, it's a case
of nine-hour shifts

02:11.599 --> 02:15.617
listening to Celine Dion
murder "O Holy Night."

02:15.619 --> 02:17.352
If I ever meet
that skinny bitch,

02:17.354 --> 02:20.656
I'm going to beat
the "O Holy" crap out of her.

02:20.658 --> 02:22.791
And that's what Christmas
is all about.

02:23.878 --> 02:25.043
I'm sorry.

02:25.045 --> 02:26.962
Tell me about your day.

02:26.964 --> 02:29.864
After you left,
I made some breakfast...

02:29.866 --> 02:31.500
Oh, I got the mail.

02:31.502 --> 02:34.219
And then I did some work on
that app I've been developing,

02:34.221 --> 02:37.673
and then I did some serious
research on World War II.

02:37.675 --> 02:38.557
Really?

02:38.559 --> 02:39.675
Well, I fell asleep

02:39.677 --> 02:41.059
watching the History Channel.

02:41.061 --> 02:42.844
Sweetie, can I be honest
with you?

02:42.846 --> 02:44.396
Yeah. What's up?

02:44.398 --> 02:47.182
I am working my ass off.

02:47.184 --> 02:49.651
It would be really,
really nice if you could,

02:49.653 --> 02:52.237
I don't know,
pitch in a little.

02:52.239 --> 02:55.774
You heard the part about me
getting the mail, right?

02:57.244 --> 03:00.329
You do understand that what came
in the mail is a pile of bills?

03:00.331 --> 03:01.246
Okay...

03:01.248 --> 03:02.714
I mean, I think
it is great

03:02.716 --> 03:04.583
that you're working on
your computer stuff,

03:04.585 --> 03:06.251
but we need help now.

03:06.253 --> 03:07.786
I get it.
Say no more.

03:07.788 --> 03:10.756
I'll start looking
for a job.

03:10.758 --> 03:11.873
Thank you.

03:11.875 --> 03:13.742
And don't worry,
it's not like

03:13.744 --> 03:15.093
I expect you to make
a million dollars or anything.

03:15.095 --> 03:17.512
Oh, thank God!

03:19.016 --> 03:21.433
Go ahead. I'm going
to go run a bath.

03:21.435 --> 03:24.970
I reek of comfort and joy.

03:26.522 --> 03:28.390
Hey, Billy. What's up?

03:28.392 --> 03:30.192
Nothing much--
just running our company

03:30.194 --> 03:32.060
while you take
some personal time.

03:32.062 --> 03:34.813
Why don't you just man up
and admit you're in rehab?

03:34.815 --> 03:36.398
I am not in rehab.

03:36.400 --> 03:38.951
I told you.
I'm on a spiritual journey.

03:38.953 --> 03:40.786
Spiritual journey.
Yeah, you know what?

03:40.788 --> 03:44.272
I've been on four of those.
I still wake up craving meth.

03:44.274 --> 03:46.325
I call it "Eat, Pray, Love,

03:46.327 --> 03:49.795
Have Angry Sex
with an Asian Hooker."

03:49.797 --> 03:50.879
What do you want, Billy?

03:50.881 --> 03:52.514
Well, I'm just keeping
you in the loop

03:52.516 --> 03:53.815
about what's
going on around here.

03:53.817 --> 03:55.300
We got new computers
in the bullpen.

03:55.302 --> 03:56.785
We got a staple-less stapler.

03:56.787 --> 03:58.253
Mark Zuckerberg offered to buy

03:58.255 --> 04:00.172
a controlling interest
in the company for 800 million,

04:00.174 --> 04:04.393
and the redhead in marketing
is not wearing bras.

04:04.395 --> 04:05.960
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

04:05.962 --> 04:09.297
There's a staple-less stapler?

04:09.299 --> 04:11.633
I think we should
take his offer.

04:11.635 --> 04:13.935
Billy, we built the Electric
Suitcase from the ground up.

04:13.937 --> 04:15.737
I mean, besides,
we've been here before.

04:15.739 --> 04:17.822
You hated the fact
that I sold our last company

04:17.825 --> 04:19.940
and I've come to realize
that you were right.

04:19.942 --> 04:22.294
I hated Tarnell, the gangsta
who sold me crack,

04:22.296 --> 04:24.279
but I was still happy
to work with him.

04:24.281 --> 04:26.665
I mean, look,
this is a good offer.

04:26.667 --> 04:27.749
We should take it.

04:27.751 --> 04:29.084
Okay.

04:29.086 --> 04:32.454
Tell him 1.2 billion,
but we keep control.

04:32.456 --> 04:34.489
Where do you think we're
going to get a better offer?

04:34.491 --> 04:36.625
Bath's ready.
Want to join me?

04:36.627 --> 04:39.428
I just got a better offer.
Good-bye.

